5.description:
Requisition ID: 88006

Join the Global Community of Scotiabankers to help customers become better off.

Job Summary :

This position reports directly to the Assistant Manager, Trust Accounting. In following general accounting principles (GAAP) the Senior Trust Accountant controls the maintenance, reconciliation, accuracy and balancing of all daily functions within the Trust department.

Responsibilities of the Department :
• Preparing/reviewing net cash movements for all the funds based on transaction data;
• Preparing/reviewing G/L entries on a daily/weekly basis for any accounts assigned;
• Balancing/reviewing the daily transactions for all the funds
• Inputting or importing G/L entries into SUN;
• QC report from Sun after inputting to ensure accuracy, after completion post to G/L;
• Posting the imported G/L entries into SUN and creating the daily and weekly files for analysis;
• Preparing daily bank reconciliation and updating the outstanding cheque list;
• Reconciliation and... remittance of government accounts, preparing withholding tax;
• Quarterly reconciliation of the taxes per iFAST and the MagMedia files that would be sent to the government
• Preparing invoices or payments for commission and trailer fees,
• Reviewing daily/weekly G/L entries for completeness and accuracy,
• Analysis of various G/L accounts and following up with the outstanding items to ensure timely clearing of items;
• Reviewing various G/L analysis for accuracy and completeness;
• Manual payments to clients, custodians & FundServ.
• Updating issued manual payments and cancelled cheques into unitholder systems (IFAST, ECS & BNS) as required;
• Ensuring accuracy of daily deposits;
• Daily reconciliation of Loss/NSF fees which are allocated to funds;
• Monthly interest allocation is determined & given to the funds;
• Daily/weekly/monthly administrative tasks as assigned;
• Participating in special projects and other administrative duties as required;

Requirements :
• Excellent problem-solving skills;
• Strong verbal & written communication skills;
• Ability to multi-task in a fast pace environment;
• Excellent time management & organizational skills;

Qualifications :
• College Diploma
• Level 2 CGA – definite asset
• IFIC operations certified definite asset;
• Min 1 yr experience in the mutual funds industry experience required;
• Experience working with ( SUN, & Ifast) – definite asset ;
• Proficiency MS Office (i.e. excel & word) required;
• Experience working within a team environment

6.description:
Staffing Consultant, Accounting

As a Staffing Consultant, you will spend your time on business development activities, sourcing and recruiting the perfect candidates on behalf of our clients to accelerate their success. This entails spending a large portion of your time on the phone, establishing connections with potential candidates. You will conduct telephone and face-to-face meetings to establish relationships with your candidates and gain an in-depth understanding of their wants, needs and cultural 'fit'. Your role is to be both an advisor to, and an advocate for, the companies looking to hire top-tier talent, and the candidates you are representing.
• **This position would be ideal for someone who is comfortable working from home, who has a strong recruitment and sales background, and who is seeking a high commission base salary***

Responsibilities:
• Full life cycle recruiting;
• Develop and grow a client database through building client relationships, cold calling, and... networking in a specific, local territory;
• Develop and execute an outbound call strategy to generate new business;
• Consult with prospective clients to review staffing requirements and determine the best strategy for strategic sourcing;
• Develop and implement proactive recruitment strategies to build and maintain a pipeline of top talent;
• Set a high standard of excellence (positive candidate experience) to meet or exceed team quality output;
• Have involvement in the proposal process by developing and pitching proposals;
• Negotiate commercial terms of business and rates

Qualifications:
• University Degree or College Diploma in Human Resources, Business Administration or a related field;
• 1+ years of recruiting experience including sourcing and full life cycle recruiting;
• 2+ years of sales/business development experience;
• Excellent interpersonal, communication and presentation skills with an ability to engage others in a pleasant, positive and professional manner;
• Effective time management and organizational skills;
• Demonstrated ability to multi-task, be self-motivated, and work effectively with multiple deadlines and with minimal supervision;
• Working knowledge of Applicant Tracking Systems (ATS)

Inclusiveness:

At Southwest Staffing Solutions Inc., we are committed to fostering an inclusive, accessible environment, where all employees and customers feel valued, respected and supported. We are dedicated to building a workforce that reflects the diversity of our customers and communities in which we live and serve. If you require an accommodation for the recruitment/interview process (including alternate formats of materials, or accessible meeting rooms or other accommodation), please let us know and we will work with you to meet your needs
